{"pagelen": 100, "values": [{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210/comments/54121714.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt/issues/210#comment-54121714"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 210, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}ts=2272898"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "subt", "full_name": "osrf/subt", "uuid": "{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}"}, "title": "Problem building the docker solution images based on a local file system"}, "content": {"raw": "You should be able to use the COPY command in the Dockerfile to copy files locally to the image.  There is an example at the end of the subt/docker/subt\\_team\\_entry/Dockerfile where it copies the entry point from the local file system to the image.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>You should be able to use the COPY command in the Dockerfile to copy files locally to the image.  There is an example at the end of the subt/docker/subt_team_entry/Dockerfile where it copies the entry point from the local file system to the image.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-09-29T15:54:49.610599+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "GoRobotGo", "uuid": "{2fd8dac8-286d-461a-b7dd-dba99deea025}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2fd8dac8-286d-461a-b7dd-dba99deea025%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2fd8dac8-286d-461a-b7dd-dba99deea025%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/6431739b101c18640b5a84d359fdd274d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsG-4.png"}}, "nickname": "GoRobotGo", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:44b40072-c04b-41ae-ad09-376db9ebffa1"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 54121714}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210/comments/54121813.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt/issues/210#comment-54121813"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 210, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}ts=2272898"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "subt", "full_name": "osrf/subt", "uuid": "{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}"}, "title": "Problem building the docker solution images based on a local file system"}, "content": {"raw": null, "markup": "markdown", "html": "", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-09-29T16:21:48.560586+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Alfredo Bencomo", "uuid": "{84891a71-dff2-4b97-8891-9446c16e6f89}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B84891a71-dff2-4b97-8891-9446c16e6f89%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B84891a71-dff2-4b97-8891-9446c16e6f89%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/5cf75629ff02b50ea27b2817/82be1d48-d490-4d7b-8ddb-a8093b9417a6/128"}}, "nickname": "bencomo", "type": "user", "account_id": "5cf75629ff02b50ea27b2817"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 54121813}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210/comments/54121968.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt/issues/210#comment-54121968"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 210, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}ts=2272898"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "subt", "full_name": "osrf/subt", "uuid": "{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}"}, "title": "Problem building the docker solution images based on a local file system"}, "content": {"raw": "Thank you very much for the hint. We tried to use COPY, but we were only able to copy files that are positioned in the folder where the DOCKERFILE is stored. This seems to me also the case in the example in subt\\_team\\_entry. Using ../../ with COPY creates an error.\n\nI will try to explain our problem in more detail: We have one project that was based on subt\\_seed where all the source-files are stored on the local file system. For the submission of our solution we need a docker image for each robot. To be able to use the COPY command it seems that we need to copy the source-files in every docker-image-build-folder to have them available during the docker - build process. \n\nIs there a special option for using COPY or is there another solution for this?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Thank you very much for the hint. We tried to use COPY, but we were only able to copy files that are positioned in the folder where the DOCKERFILE is stored. This seems to me also the case in the example in subt_team_entry. Using ../../ with COPY creates an error.</p>\n<p>I will try to explain our problem in more detail: We have one project that was based on subt_seed where all the source-files are stored on the local file system. For the submission of our solution we need a docker image for each robot. To be able to use the COPY command it seems that we need to copy the source-files in every docker-image-build-folder to have them available during the docker - build process. </p>\n<p>Is there a special option for using COPY or is there another solution for this?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-09-29T16:55:29.694634+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Sophisticated Engineering", "uuid": "{12ed2357-e253-4c67-a2b9-7e12c64773e4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B12ed2357-e253-4c67-a2b9-7e12c64773e4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B12ed2357-e253-4c67-a2b9-7e12c64773e4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2a19963da6b0f34b3be28d8690bdd711d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSE-6.png"}}, "nickname": "sopheng", "type": "user", "account_id": "5c0d82b3128c7106f57691a7"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 54121968}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210/comments/54122058.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt/issues/210#comment-54122058"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 210, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}ts=2272898"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "subt", "full_name": "osrf/subt", "uuid": "{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}"}, "title": "Problem building the docker solution images based on a local file system"}, "content": {"raw": "Try with the [ADD](https://docs.docker.com/v17.09/engine/reference/builder/#add) command instead; which copies files from the host machine into the docker image.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Try with the <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"https://docs.docker.com/v17.09/engine/reference/builder/#add\" rel=\"nofollow\">ADD</a> command instead; which copies files from the host machine into the docker image.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-09-29T17:08:52.197465+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Alfredo Bencomo", "uuid": "{84891a71-dff2-4b97-8891-9446c16e6f89}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B84891a71-dff2-4b97-8891-9446c16e6f89%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B84891a71-dff2-4b97-8891-9446c16e6f89%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/5cf75629ff02b50ea27b2817/82be1d48-d490-4d7b-8ddb-a8093b9417a6/128"}}, "nickname": "bencomo", "type": "user", "account_id": "5cf75629ff02b50ea27b2817"}, "updated_on": "2019-09-29T17:12:10.309352+00:00", "type": "issue_comment", "id": 54122058}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210/comments/54122081.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt/issues/210#comment-54122081"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 210, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}ts=2272898"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "subt", "full_name": "osrf/subt", "uuid": "{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}"}, "title": "Problem building the docker solution images based on a local file system"}, "content": {"raw": "Based on my limited understanding of docker, I think your proposed solution is the only way I know how.  You cp your source to the docker-image-build-folder and then use the COPY command to move it in.  You could add that cp step to the build script.  There is also a docker ADD command that accepts a url.  Maybe if you had a local webserver running you could use that.  Beyond that I will have to defer to the docker experts.\n\n\u200c", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Based on my limited understanding of docker, I think your proposed solution is the only way I know how.  You cp your source to the docker-image-build-folder and then use the COPY command to move it in.  You could add that cp step to the build script.  There is also a docker ADD command that accepts a url.  Maybe if you had a local webserver running you could use that.  Beyond that I will have to defer to the docker experts.</p>\n<p>\u200c</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-09-29T17:13:23.291701+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "GoRobotGo", "uuid": "{2fd8dac8-286d-461a-b7dd-dba99deea025}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2fd8dac8-286d-461a-b7dd-dba99deea025%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2fd8dac8-286d-461a-b7dd-dba99deea025%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/6431739b101c18640b5a84d359fdd274d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsG-4.png"}}, "nickname": "GoRobotGo", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:44b40072-c04b-41ae-ad09-376db9ebffa1"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 54122081}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210/comments/54122283.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt/issues/210#comment-54122283"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 210, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}ts=2272898"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "subt", "full_name": "osrf/subt", "uuid": "{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}"}, "title": "Problem building the docker solution images based on a local file system"}, "content": {"raw": "@{5cf75629ff02b50ea27b2817} For my understanding the ADD command has the same limitations as the COPY command only that also URLs are possible. Or is it possible to use there ../../?\n\n@{557058:44b40072-c04b-41ae-ad09-376db9ebffa1}  Thanks. We didn\u2019t want to change the build.bash script. And we thought there must be an easier solution :disappointed:", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p><span class=\"ap-mention\" data-atlassian-id=\"5cf75629ff02b50ea27b2817\">@Alfredo Bencomo</span> For my understanding the ADD command has the same limitations as the COPY command only that also URLs are possible. Or is it possible to use there ../../?</p>\n<p><span class=\"ap-mention\" data-atlassian-id=\"557058:44b40072-c04b-41ae-ad09-376db9ebffa1\">@GoRobotGo</span>  Thanks. We didn\u2019t want to change the build.bash script. And we thought there must be an easier solution <img class=\"emoji\" src=\"data/pf-emoji-service--cdn.us-east-1.prod.public.atl-paas.net/standard/551c9814-1d37-4573-819d-afab3afeaf32/48x48/1f61e.png\" alt=\"\ud83d\ude1e\" title=\":disappointed:\" data-emoji-short-name=\":disappointed:\" /></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-09-29T17:36:37.894409+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Sophisticated Engineering", "uuid": "{12ed2357-e253-4c67-a2b9-7e12c64773e4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B12ed2357-e253-4c67-a2b9-7e12c64773e4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B12ed2357-e253-4c67-a2b9-7e12c64773e4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2a19963da6b0f34b3be28d8690bdd711d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSE-6.png"}}, "nickname": "sopheng", "type": "user", "account_id": "5c0d82b3128c7106f57691a7"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 54122283}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210/comments/54124555.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt/issues/210#comment-54124555"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 210, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}ts=2272898"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "subt", "full_name": "osrf/subt", "uuid": "{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}"}, "title": "Problem building the docker solution images based on a local file system"}, "content": {"raw": "You cannot perform any operations outside of the docker build index used when you build you docker image.\n\nIf you want to do a `COPY` operation from a directory above \\(i.e. `../`\\) you need to run your Docker build from the `../` directory or modify your `build.bash` script if you\u2019re utilizing that. I was forced to do this with a single directory up in the `subt_hello_world` repository.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>You cannot perform any operations outside of the docker build index used when you build you docker image.</p>\n<p>If you want to do a <code>COPY</code> operation from a directory above (i.e. <code>../</code>) you need to run your Docker build from the <code>../</code> directory or modify your <code>build.bash</code> script if you\u2019re utilizing that. I was forced to do this with a single directory up in the <code>subt_hello_world</code> repository.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-09-30T02:41:35.634313+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Arthur Schang", "uuid": "{1403972a-9b64-442b-a69c-d7e9557e1d87}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B1403972a-9b64-442b-a69c-d7e9557e1d87%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B1403972a-9b64-442b-a69c-d7e9557e1d87%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/initials/AS-0.png"}}, "nickname": "Arthur Schang", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:14b7fd50-d65a-47a8-825c-fa89681d07bd"}, "updated_on": "2019-09-30T02:42:16.906237+00:00", "type": "issue_comment", "id": 54124555}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210/comments/54126199.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt/issues/210#comment-54126199"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 210, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}ts=2272898"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "subt", "full_name": "osrf/subt", "uuid": "{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}"}, "title": "Problem building the docker solution images based on a local file system"}, "content": {"raw": "@{557058:14b7fd50-d65a-47a8-825c-fa89681d07bd} : Thanks for the explanation. I\u2019ll have a look into the `build.bash` script in the `subt_hello_world` repository", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p><span class=\"ap-mention\" data-atlassian-id=\"557058:14b7fd50-d65a-47a8-825c-fa89681d07bd\">@Arthur Schang</span> : Thanks for the explanation. I\u2019ll have a look into the <code>build.bash</code> script in the <code>subt_hello_world</code> repository</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-09-30T06:24:03.806303+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Sophisticated Engineering", "uuid": "{12ed2357-e253-4c67-a2b9-7e12c64773e4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B12ed2357-e253-4c67-a2b9-7e12c64773e4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B12ed2357-e253-4c67-a2b9-7e12c64773e4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2a19963da6b0f34b3be28d8690bdd711d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSE-6.png"}}, "nickname": "sopheng", "type": "user", "account_id": "5c0d82b3128c7106f57691a7"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 54126199}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210/comments/54294774.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt/issues/210#comment-54294774"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 210, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}ts=2272898"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "subt", "full_name": "osrf/subt", "uuid": "{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}"}, "title": "Problem building the docker solution images based on a local file system"}, "content": {"raw": "It looks like Arthur resolved this issue.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>It looks like Arthur resolved this issue.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-10-10T17:09:31.986746+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Nate Koenig", "uuid": "{c862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:095b1e12-74ed-4e20-b44f-2f0745b616e0/ca24bb11-4787-4b14-a20d-d91835e9bde2/128"}}, "nickname": "Nathan Koenig", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:095b1e12-74ed-4e20-b44f-2f0745b616e0"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 54294774}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210/comments/54609718.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt/issues/210#comment-54609718"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/210.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 210, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}ts=2272898"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "subt", "full_name": "osrf/subt", "uuid": "{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}"}, "title": "Problem building the docker solution images based on a local file system"}, "content": {"raw": null, "markup": "markdown", "html": "", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-10-31T05:47:20.280447+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Alfredo Bencomo", "uuid": "{84891a71-dff2-4b97-8891-9446c16e6f89}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B84891a71-dff2-4b97-8891-9446c16e6f89%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B84891a71-dff2-4b97-8891-9446c16e6f89%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/5cf75629ff02b50ea27b2817/82be1d48-d490-4d7b-8ddb-a8093b9417a6/128"}}, "nickname": "bencomo", "type": "u